**README.md serves as npm package landing page and user onboarding guide for agents-reverse-engineer CLI tool, documenting installation workflows, command reference, configuration schema, and AI assistant integration patterns.**

## Package Identity

Repository name: `agents-reverse-engineer` (ARE)

npm package: `agents-reverse-engineer`

Supported AI runtimes: Claude Code, OpenCode, Gemini CLI, any tool supporting `AGENTS.md` format

Installation entry point: `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest` (interactive installer)

Binary commands: `are` (primary), `agents-reverse-engineer` (alias)

License: MIT

Node.js requirement: ≥18.0.0

## Installation Workflows

Interactive mode: `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest` prompts for runtime selection (claude/opencode/gemini/all) and location (-g global vs -l local)

Non-interactive install: `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest --runtime <rt> {-g|-l}` with explicit runtime and scope

Uninstall: `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest uninstall` removes command files, session hooks, ARE permissions from settings.json, and `.agents-reverse-engineer` folder (local installs only)

Version check: `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest --version`

Global install paths: `~/.claude/`, `~/.config/opencode/`, `~/.gemini/`

Local install paths: `./.claude/`, `./.opencode/`, `./.gemini/`

## CLI Command Reference

`are install` — Interactive installer with runtime/location prompts

`are install --runtime <rt> -g` — Install to specified runtime globally

`are install --runtime <rt> -l` — Install to specified runtime locally

`are install -u` — Uninstall (remove files/hooks)

`are init` — Create `.agents-reverse-engineer/config.yaml` with defaults

`are discover` — List files for analysis respecting `.gitignore`

`are discover --plan` — Generate `GENERATION-PLAN.md` with post-order directory traversal

`are discover --show-excluded` — Display excluded files with exclusion reasons

`are generate` — Three-phase pipeline: `.sum` files → `AGENTS.md` → root docs (CLAUDE.md/GEMINI.md/OPENCODE.md)

`are update` — Incremental regeneration for changed files only

`are specify` — Synthesize all `AGENTS.md` into `specs/SPEC.md` (use `--multi-file` for split output, `--dry-run` for preview)

`are clean` — Remove all generated documentation artifacts

## AI Assistant Slash Commands

`/are-init` — Initialize configuration (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

`/are-discover` — Rediscover and regenerate plan (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

`/are-generate` — Generate all documentation (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

`/are-update` — Update changed files only (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

`/are-specify` — Generate project specification (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

`/are-clean` — Remove all generated docs (supported: Claude, OpenCode, Gemini)

Command locations: `.claude/skills/are-*/SKILL.md` (Claude), `.opencode/commands/are-*.md` (OpenCode), `.gemini/commands/are-*.toml` (Gemini)

## Configuration Schema

Config file: `.agents-reverse-engineer/config.yaml`

`exclude.patterns` — Custom glob patterns (e.g., `["*.log", "temp/**"]`)

`exclude.vendorDirs` — Directories to skip (default includes node_modules, dist, .git)

`exclude.binaryExtensions` — File types to skip (default includes .png, .jpg, .pdf)

`options.followSymlinks` — Boolean, default `false`

`options.maxFileSize` — Bytes, default `1048576` (1MB)

`output.colors` — Boolean, terminal ANSI color codes

`output.verbose` — Boolean, show each file during processing

`ai.backend` — Backend selector: `'claude'` | `'gemini'` | `'opencode'` | `'auto'`

`ai.model` — Model identifier (backend-specific, e.g., `'sonnet'`)

`ai.timeoutMs` — Subprocess timeout, default `300000` (5 minutes)

`ai.maxRetries` — Max retry attempts, default `3`

`ai.concurrency` — Parallel AI calls, range `1-10`, default `5` (reduced to `2` in WSL environments)

`ai.telemetry.keepRuns` — Retention count for run logs, default `50`

`ai.telemetry.costThresholdUsd` — Warning threshold for cumulative costs, default `10.0`

`ai.pricing` — Custom model pricing overrides with keys `inputCostPerMTok`, `outputCostPerMTok` (USD per 1M tokens)

## Generated Documentation Formats

`.sum` files: YAML frontmatter (`file_type`, `generated_at`) followed by markdown sections (Purpose, Public Interface, Dependencies, Implementation Notes)

`AGENTS.md`: Directory overview with role description, files grouped by purpose (Types/Services/Utils), subdirectories with descriptions

`CLAUDE.md`: Claude Code project entry point (auto-loaded)

`GEMINI.md`: Gemini CLI project entry point

`OPENCODE.md`: OpenCode project entry point

Root `AGENTS.md`: Universal format directory overview for root directory

## Three-Phase Generation Pipeline

Phase 1 — File Analysis: Creates `.sum` file for each source file (concurrent execution)

Phase 2 — Directory Docs: Creates `AGENTS.md` for each directory (post-order traversal, deepest first)

Phase 3 — Root Docs: Creates `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `OPENCODE.md` (sequential execution)

Post-order traversal ensures child documentation exists before parent directories are documented

## Incremental Update Strategy

`/are-update` command compares SHA-256 content hashes from `.sum` YAML frontmatter against current file content

Only regenerates documentation for files with hash mismatches (status: `'modified'` or `'added'`)

Detects orphans: `.sum` files for deleted source files or renamed oldPaths

Cleanup operations: `cleanupOrphans()` deletes stale `.sum` files, `cleanupEmptyDirectoryDocs()` removes `AGENTS.md` from directories with no remaining sources

Computes `affectedDirs` via `getAffectedDirectories()` by walking parent directories of changed files

## Session Hooks

Claude/Gemini session lifecycle integration: Auto-updates docs when session ends if changes detected

Hook detection for installation: Session hook installed during `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest` workflow for Claude and Gemini runtimes

OpenCode plugin system: Hooks not mentioned for OpenCode (command-based integration only)

## Resource Constraints

Concurrency default changed from `5` to `2` in WSL environments for memory management

Lower concurrency recommended for resource-constrained environments

Higher concurrency values speed up generation but increase memory usage

Timeout increased from default 120s (documented elsewhere) to 300s (5 minutes) in config reference